  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, your team made it to the top 4 by two runs, amazing win! What part of the match was the most exciting for you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The final over was really nail-biting. Our bowler, Ishant, took two wickets in the last over. It was *aadhichya* moment!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That was intense, bowlers under pressure are magic to watch. Who’s your pick for the next match’s hero?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think Virat has been in great form. He can change the game in 20 balls. But honestly, our bowlers are *unstoppable* right now. Maybe both?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s a great mix of trust, batting and bowling in sync is a winning combo. What’s your go to snack while watching such matches?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually have some *pakodas* and tea. It’s messy but keeps me going. Oh, and popcorn if it’s a long match. You?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I love pakodas and tea, the perfect match snack. I stick to tea most of the time. What’s your favorite pakoda flavor?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite is *aloo bhindi* pakoda. Sometimes I can’t choose and just get a mix. The spices make them so addictive!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Aloo bhindi pakodas are a classic, spicy and crispy, hard to stop at one. Do you make them at home or buy from a street vendor?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Mostly from a street vendor near my office. They make it *crunchy* and hot. But I try to make them at home on weekends. Not as good, though. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Street vendor pakodas are unbeatable, that’s why we keep going back! What’s the one dish you *always* make at home on weekends?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I make *rajma* on weekends. It takes time but is worth it. My mom’s recipe — slow cooked, spicy, and *delicious*. No street vendor can match that! 😄"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Rajma cooked the old school way is a comfort, slow cooking makes all the difference. What’s your favorite way to enjoy it, with rice or roti?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "With rice for sure. The way it soaks up the gravy... *mazaak*! Sometimes I add a boiled egg on top. Simple but hits the spot after a long week."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds comforting, rice soaking up all the flavor, and the egg on top is a smart touch. What’s your go to lazy weekend meal besides rajma?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Pav bhaji! Spicy, messy, and so satisfying. I just add a bit of *chaat masala* and relish. Easy, quick, and makes me feel like I'm in Mumbai again. 🍛"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Pav bhaji with chaat masala is a Mumbai memory in every bite, messy and perfect! What’s your favorite side to have with it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually have *masala chaas* or a simple salad. The chaas cools down the spice, and the salad adds a fresh crunch. Both are *aamcha* (normal) but make the meal complete. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Masala chaas and salad are the perfect balance, spice and fresh all in one meal. What’s your favorite movie to watch after a meal like this?"
    }
  ],
